Grupo Financiero Santander Mexico S.A. B. de C.V. (BSMX) & Banco Santander Brasil SA (BSBR) Financial Survey

					Posted by Brenda Bartman on Jul 21st, 2017 // No Comments 



Banco Santander Brasil SA (NYSE: BSBR) and Grupo Financiero Santander Mexico S.A. B. de C.V. (NYSE:BSMX) are both large-cap finance companies, but which is the superior investment? We will contrast the two businesses based on the strength of their earnings, institutional ownership, profitabiliy, valuation, dividends, analyst recommendations and risk. 
Profitability


 Get Banco Santander Brasil SA alerts:



This table compares Banco Santander Brasil SA and Grupo Financiero Santander Mexico S.A. B. de C.V.’s net margins, return on equity and return on assets.



Net Margins
Return on Equity
Return on Assets


Banco Santander Brasil SA
8.16%
8.76%
1.23%


Grupo Financiero Santander Mexico S.A. B. de C.V.
16.29%
14.09%
1.27%






Dividends
Banco Santander Brasil SA pays an annual dividend of $0.09 per share and has a dividend yield of 1.1%. Grupo Financiero Santander Mexico S.A. B. de C.V. pays an annual dividend of $0.55 per share and has a dividend yield of 5.2%. Banco Santander Brasil SA pays out 20.5% of its earnings in the form of a dividend. Grupo Financiero Santander Mexico S.A. B. de C.V. pays out 87.3% of its earnings in the form of a dividend, suggesting it may not have sufficient earnings to cover its dividend payment in the future. 
Analyst Ratings
This is a breakdown of current recommendations for Banco Santander Brasil SA and Grupo Financiero Santander Mexico S.A. B. de C.V., as provided by MarketBeat. 



Sell Ratings
Hold Ratings
Buy Ratings
Strong Buy Ratings
