2.25


Banco Santander Brasil SA presently has a consensus target price of $13.15, suggesting a potential upside of 60.76%. Grupo Financiero Santander Mexico S.A. B. de C.V. has a consensus target price of $7.80, suggesting a potential downside of 25.86%. Given Banco Santander Brasil SA’s  higher probable upside, analysts clearly believe Banco Santander Brasil SA is more favorable than Grupo Financiero Santander Mexico S.A. B. de C.V..
Risk and Volatility
Banco Santander Brasil SA has a beta of 1.54, indicating that its stock price is 54% more volatile than the S&P 500. Comparatively, Grupo Financiero Santander Mexico S.A. B. de C.V. has a beta of 1.38, indicating that its stock price is 38% more volatile than the S&P 500. 
Insider & Institutional Ownership
0.9% of Banco Santander Brasil SA shares are owned by institutional investors. Comparatively, 32.7% of Grupo Financiero Santander Mexico S.A. B. de C.V. shares are owned by institutional investors. Strong institutional ownership is an indication that large money managers, hedge funds and endowments believe a stock will outperform the market over the long term.
Earnings & Valuation
This table compares Banco Santander Brasil SA and Grupo Financiero Santander Mexico S.A. B. de C.V.’s gross revenue, earnings per share and valuation.



