Grupo Financiero Santander Mexico SAB de CV

Roana De Caro |
Lunes, Julio 24, 2017







$0.17 EPS Expected for Santander Mexico Fincl Gp SAB deCV (ADR) (BSMX)
The company has a 50-day moving average of $9.68 and a 200 day moving average of $8.58.Shares of Grupo Simec SAB de CV (NYSEMKT:SIM) traded down 1.37% during midday trading on Monday, hitting $10.82.
The Guadalajara, Mexico-based company said it had net income of 20 cents per share.These firms have also modified their investment in BSMX. Virtu Financial LLC purchased a new stake in Grupo Financiero Santander Mexico S.A. B.de C.V. during the second quarter worth approximately $364,000. Aperio Group LLC now owns 58,074 shares of the bank's stock worth $560,000 after buying an additional 5,518 shares during the period. The value of the position overall is up by 17.9%. Huntington National Bank increased its stake in shares of Grupo Financiero Santander Mexico S.A. B.de C.V.by 4.1% in the second quarter. The value of the company's investment in Grupo Financiero Santander Mexi went from $103,000 to $115,000 a change of $12,000 quarter over quarter.Eqis Capital Management, Inc. bolstered its ownership by buying 1,161 shares an increase of 3.0%. Eqis Capital Management, Inc. owns 39,668 shares with a value of $382,000. Zacks Investment Research now has $11.00 price target on the bank's stock. On September 7, 2016 the stock rating was rated "Neutral" according to a UBS report which was a cut from the previous " rating.On January 11 the stock rating was upgraded from "Underperform" to "Neutral" in a statement from Bank of America.5/4/2017-J P Morgan Chase & Co Upgrade from a "Neutral " rating to a " Overweight" rating.The company is trading up by 2.23% since yesterday's close of $10.33. Additionally the company declared a dividend for shareholders paid on Tuesday the 6th of June 2017. The dividend payment was $0.163 per share for the quarter which comes to $0.65 on an annualized basis. The ex-dividend date was set for Wednesday the 24th of May 2017. The stock's market capitalization is 1.81B. As of the last earnings report the EPS was $0.71 and is estimated to be $0.66 for the current year with 1,355,516,000 shares now outstanding. Next quarter's EPS is forecasted to be $0.17 with next year's EPS projected to be $0.77.Grupo Financiero Santander Mexico S.A. B.de C.V. (NYSE:BSMX) has earned a consensus rating of "Hold" from the six ratings firms that are now covering the firm, Marketbeat reports. The Company operates through two segments Mexican and USA. The company offers various deposit products, such as current accounts, savings accounts, and time deposits, as well as certificates of interbank deposit; and payroll loans, personal loans, credit cards, mortgages, and insurance brokerage services. The Firm is primarily engaged in the provision of multiple banking services, securities brokerage, financial advice services, as well as other related investment activities. The Company offers its services to both, individual and corporate clients. As of December 31, 2015, it had 1,354 offices and 5,989 ATMs in Mexico. Citigroup Inc. upgraded Grupo Financiero Santander Mexico S.A. B.de C.V. from a "neutral" rating to a "buy" rating in a research note on Thursday. The company was founded in 1991 and is headquartered in Mexico City, Mexico. BidaskClub raised shares of Grupo Simec SAB de CV from a "sell" rating to a "hold" rating in a research report on Tuesday, June 13th.




